==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Keckle
<hw>Kec"kle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Keckled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Keckling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>To wind old rope around, as a cable, to preserve its surface from
being fretted, or to wind iron chains around, to defend from the
friction of a rocky bottom, or from the ice.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keckling</ent>⟦br⟧
